This paper discusses the use of blockchain technology in IoT networks, which involves security and networking aspects. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses the use of distributed consensus mechanisms, which falls under the category of cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). Additionally, the paper proposes a layered architecture, which involves software engineering aspects and falls under the category of cs.SE (Software Engineering). The paper also discusses the evaluation of the proposed modules, which involves data analysis and falls under the category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper discusses the use of blockchain in IoT networks, which involves networking aspects and falls under the category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture).
